<TITLE> Security for KPIs, VIPs to be heightened </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Metropolitan Police on Friday decided to heighten security for important people and at key point installations. The decision came from a special meeting, chaired by the acting capital's police chief Abul Kashem and attended by the high officials of the intelligence agencies and chiefs of the 40 police stations, additional deputy commissioner Walid Hossain said. The meeting discussed the current law and order status and decided to be strict to combat clashes, attempts to create panic and activities of the banned organisations, the DMP spokesman said. Officers-in-charge of the police stations were ordered to strictly adhere to the instructions. On Thursday night, the government ordered law enforcers countrywide to be on extra alert due to the Bangabandhu murder case proceedings and the recent bomb attack on Awami League MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh, home minister Sahara Khatun said. Sahara told bdnews24.com on Thursday night, "The government was already conscious of security issues from the start of the case proceedings." "But law enforcing agencies, including RAB and police, have been given directions to be more alert." "Security has been tightened at all key points and installations in the capital and around the country," she said. Home secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder also told bdnews24.com security at the prisons where the death convicts are being held had been tightened. He said meetings headed by the home minister were held at the secretariat on Thursday with the heads of different law enforcing agencies. bdn
